 and in the provincial town of Nullangardie. The men range in age from their early twenties to sixty, in class from working class to jaded hustler, in sexual role from drag queen to happily married bisexual. The men reveal how they came to their homosexuality, how they understand the AIDS crisis, and how they have reacted to the crisis in terms of their sexual practice. The men tell their own tales, describing their sex lives in graphic detail and uninhibited language.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aMEDICAL / Health Care Delivery.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150361616540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503616165423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503616165/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles